## 🌳 Traversing the DOM

```js
const parent = document.querySelector(".container");

// Children
parent.children           // HTMLCollection of child elements
parent.firstElementChild  // first child element
parent.lastElementChild   // last child element
parent.childNodes         // includes text nodes & comments

// Parent
element.parentElement     // direct parent element
element.parentNode        // direct parent node

// Siblings
element.nextElementSibling     // next element sibling
element.previousElementSibling // previous element sibling

// Check matches
element.matches(".active")     // true/false — CSS selector check
element.closest(".card")       // nearest ancestor matching selector
```

